                temperature zones, allowing for the storage of both red and
                white wines at their respective ideal temperatures. Common
                repair needs for wine coolers include thermostat issues, which
                can lead to temperature fluctuations and potentially spoil the
                wine. Problems with the cooling system, such as a failing
                compressor or evaporator fan, can also affect the unit's
                performance. Regular maintenance, including cleaning the
                condenser coils and ensuring proper ventilation, can help
                prevent these issues and keep wine coolers operating
                efficiently.
              </p>
